n%2C%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BWe're%20running%20out%20of%20human%20knowledge.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20solution%20is%20to%20hire%20a%20bunch%20of%20humans%20to%20literally%20churn%20out%20new%20knowledge%20and%20then%20pump%20that%20into%20the%20AI%20model%20training%20process.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20so%20gated%20on%20data%20that%20they're%20literally%20going%20out%20and%20hiring%20thousands%20of%20programmers%20and%20doctors%20and%20lawyers%20to%20actually%20hand%20write%20answers%20to%20questions%20for%20the%20purpose%20of%20being%20able%20to%20train%20their%20AIs%2C%26quot%3B%20Andreessen%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20at%20that%20level%20of%20constraints.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20not%20the%20future%20that%20was%20feared%20when%20OpenAI's%20ChatGPT%20burst%20onto%20the%20scene%20almost%20two%20years%20ago.%20Since%20then%2C%20dire%20warnings%20of%20job%20destruction%20have%20been%20issued%2C%20with%20lists%20(published%20by%20Business%20Insider%20and%20other%20publications)%20predicting%20roles%20in%20areas%20such%20as%20coding%20and%20law%20would%20succumb%20to%20the%20AI%20job%20apocalypse.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20least%20for%20now%2C%20some%20of%20these%20professions%20are%20needed%20to%20help%20feed%20new%20AI%20models%20with%20fresh%2C%20accurate%20human%20data.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20irony%20of%20this%20was%20not%20lost%20on%C2%A0Andreessen%20and%20Horowitz%2C%20who%20chuckled%20during%20the%20podcast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWell%2C%20actually%2C%20this%20is%20also%20part%20of%20one%20of%20the%20big%20fears%20is%20AI%20driven%20unemployment%2C%20and%20the%20irony%20is%20what's%20happening%20today%20is%20an%20AI%20hiring%20boom%2C%26quot%3B%20Andreessen%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20a%20big%20part%20of%20the%20AI%20hiring%20boom%20is%20actually%20hiring%20the%20experts%20to%20actually%20craft%20the%20answers%20to%20be%20able%20to%20train%20the%20AI.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3