lion.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Andre%20Nader%20sat%20down%20in%202022%20to%20crunch%20what%20he%20calls%20his%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fandrenader.substack.com%2Fp%2Fmy-enough-number%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eenough%20number%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20the%20amount%20of%20money%20that%20would%20allow%20him%20to%20never%20have%20to%20earn%20another%20dollar%20%E2%80%94%20it%20came%20out%20to%20about%20%244%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20and%20his%20wife%20were%20living%20and%20working%20full-time%20in%20tech%20in%20San%20Francisco%2C%20raising%20a%20toddler%2C%20and%20loosely%20planning%20on%20eventually%20leaving%20the%20expensive%20Bay%20Area.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20two%20years%20later%2C%20Nader's%20life%20looks%20very%20different.%20Meta%20laid%20him%20off%20in%20May%202023%2C%20life%20has%20gotten%20more%20expensive%2C%20and%20he%20can%20picture%20raising%20his%20now%20six-year-old%20in%20San%20Francisco.%20His%20%26quot%3Benough%20number%26quot%3B%20is%20also%20different%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20closer%20to%20%245.6%20million%2C%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%2037-year-old%2C%20who%20worked%20in%20tech%20for%20over%2015%20years%20and%20has%20been%20writing%20about%20financial%20independence%20on%20his%20platform%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fandrenader.substack.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFAANG%20FIRE%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20since%202021%2C%20considers%20himself%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fandrenader.substack.com%2Fp%2Fofficially-semi-fired%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esemi-FIRE'd%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20layoff%2C%20Nader%20and%20his%20wife%20had%20enough%20between%20her%20tech%20income%20and%20their%20savings%20that%20he%20didn't%20have%20to%20find%20another%20job.%20They'd%20been%20preparing%20to%20retire%20early%20together%20and%20had%20already%20built%20a%20sizable%20nest%20egg.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20feel%20like%20I%20cannot%20say%20I'm%20fully%20retired%20while%20my%20wife%20is%20still%20working%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20pointing%20out%20that%2C%20%26quot%3BI've%20never%20met%20a%20stay-at-home%20mom%20who%20referred%20to%20herself%20as%20retired.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENader%20spends%20his%20days%20writing%20on%20Substack%20and%20doing%20one-on-one%20FIRE%20coaching.%20Between%20coaching%2C%20his%20paid%20Substack%20subscribers%2C%20and%20affiliate%20links%2C%20he%20said%20he%20brings%20in%20about%20%2440%2C000%20a%20year.%20He%20also%20takes%20on%20more%20of%20the%20parenting%20responsibilities.%20His%20%26quot%3Benough%20number%26quot%3B%20is%20constantly%20shifting%2C%20but%20here's%20how%20he%20came%20up%20with%20%245.6%20million%20for%20a%20family%20of%20three%20living%20in%20San%20Francisco.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228716000b-4bf7-49af-9219-1940f017ed41%5C%22%3EHow%20much%20is%20'enough'%20to%20retire%20in%20San%20Francisco%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENader's%20approach%20to%20answering%20this%20question%20involves%20three%20main%20factors%3A%20annual%20spend%2C%20healthcare%2C%20and%20education.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22andre%20nader%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67350053ede4eeae392741a4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENader%20says%20he%20has%20assumed%20more%20parenting%20responsibilities%20since%20getting%20laid%20off%20from%20Meta%20in%202023.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Andre%20Nader%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20want%20a%20number%20that%20represents%20me%20not%20having%20to%20make%20sacrifices%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fandrenader.substack.com%2Fp%2Fenough-to-fire-in-san-francisco%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehe%20writes%20on%20his%20blog%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20want%20to%20be%20able%20to%20eat%20avocado%20toast%20every%20day%20while%20being%2030%20minutes%20from%20the%20beach%20without%20needing%20to%20work.%26quot%3B%20He%20also%20wants%20to%20be%20able%20to%20afford%20good%20healthcare%20and%20cover%20his%20daughter's%20future%20education%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cb9f2e77-a31d-448f-bf9e-558835fac480%5C%22%3EAnnual%20spend%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENader%20first%20considered%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fandrenader.substack.com%2Fp%2Fhow-much-we-spend-as-a-family-in%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehow%20much%20his%20family%20spends%20a%20year%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%2C%20at%20the%20time%2C%20came%20out%20to%20%24140%2C000.%20That%20number%20allows%20you%20to%20work%20backward%20to%20determine%20how%20big%20of%20a%20nest%20egg%20you'd%20need%20to%20maintain%20that%20level%20of%20spending%20in%20retirement.%20Many%20members%20of%20the%20FIRE%20community%20use%20the%20%26quot%3B4%25%20rule%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20suggests%20that%20you%20can%20safely%20withdraw%204%25%20annually%20from%20your%20nest%20egg.%20For%20example%2C%20if%20you%20retire%20with%20%241%20million%2C%20you%20should%20be%20able%20to%20withdraw%20%2440%2C000%20from%20your%20retirement%20funds%20each%20year%20without%20running%20out%20of%20money.%20To%20figure%20out%20your%20number%20using%20this%20rule%2C%20you%20simply%20multiply%20your%20annual%20spending%20by%2025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENader%20prefers%20to%20use%20a%20more%20conservative%203%25%20safe%20withdrawal%20rate%2C%20which%20you%20can%20calculate%20by%20multiplying%20your%20annual%20number%20by%2033.33.%20Spending%20%24140%2C000%20a%20year%20would%20mean%20having%20%244.67%20million%20in%20savings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d6048186-3c1d-4d59-be18-fa88b2d76bce%5C%22%3EHealthcare%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENext%2C%20Nader%20considered%20healthcare%2C%20which%20is%20%26quot%3Bthe%20biggest%20unknown%20factor%26quot%3B%20that%20early%20retirees%20deal%20with%2C%20he%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20the%20benefit%20now%20of%20the%20Affordable%20Care%20Act%20being%20able%20to%20go%20to%20the%20marketplace%20and%20estimate%20how%20much%20my%20expenses%20would%20be%2C%20assuming%20those%20subsidies%2C%20but%20those%20are%20things%20that%20can%20change.%20The%20subsidies%20could%20still%20be%20there%2C%20they%20might%20not%20be%20there%2C%20so%20being%20able%20to%20estimate%20how%20much%20I%20need%20for%20healthcare%20costs%20is%20always%20one%20that's%20tricky.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20estimate%2C%20which%20factored%20in%20healthcare%20premiums%2C%20copays%2C%20medicine%2C%20and%20out-of-pocket%20expenses%2C%20came%20to%20%2425%2C900%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20assumed%20healthcare%20would%20increase%20at%20the%20same%20rate%20of%20inflation%20and%2C%20using%20the%20same%203%25%20withdrawal%20calculation%2C%20determined%20he'd%20need%20an%20extra%20%24863%2C000%20(%2425%2C900%20x%2033.33)%20for%20this%20particular%20spending%20bucket.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223e405040-ede8-4881-bf28-2ff339246b88%5C%22%3EEducation%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20Nader's%20%26quot%3Benough%20number%26quot%3B%20factors%20in%20his%20daughter's%20education.%20He%20wants%20to%20be%20able%20to%20cover%20at%20least%20four%20years%20of%20public%20college%20in%20California.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUsing%20UC%20Berkeley's%20cost%20(including%20room%20and%20board)%20and%20adjusting%20for%20inflation%2C%20he%20budgeted%20%24321%2C000%20total.%20Assuming%20an%208%25%20annual%20return%20(he's%20investing%20this%20money%20in%20a%20529%20savings%20plan)%2C%20he'd%20need%20a%20lump%20sum%20of%20%24125%2C000%20to%20cover%20the%20%24321%2C000%20cost%20in%2012%20years%20when%20his%20daughter%20goes%20to%20college.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22andre%20nader%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6734ffeefa0140cdd5632994%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENader%20is%20saving%20for%20his%20daughter's%20future%20education%20co