ospace%20workers%20are%20in%20high%20demand%2C%20particularly%20with%20the%20region's%20booming%20space%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERivals%20like%20SpaceX%2C%20Blue%20Origin%20LLC%20and%20Amazon.com%20Inc.'s%20Project%20Kuiper%20are%20all%20searching%20for%20new%20hires%20to%20support%20rapidly%20growing%20operations%20around%20Seattle%2C%20where%20Boeing%20manufactures%20most%20of%20its%20commercial%20airplanes%2C%20said%20Stan%20Shull%2C%20a%20space%20industry%20analyst%20and%20consultant%20at%20Alliance%20Velocity%20LLC.%20The%20opportunities%20range%20from%20working%20on%20Starlink%20satellites%20for%20Elon%20Musk's%20space%20venture%20to%20helping%20with%20rockets%2C%20space%20stations%2C%20lunar%20landers%20and%20the%20like%20for%20Jeff%20Bezos's%20rival%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETight%20Market%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20about%201%2C350%20job%20openings%20at%20more%20than%2050%20space%20companies%20in%20the%20Puget%20Sound%20region%2C%20by%20Shull's%20count.%20While%20engineers%20of%20all%20stripes%20are%20in%20demand%2C%20the%20companies%20are%20also%20searching%20for%20machinists%2C%20administrative%20help%2C%20sales%20and%20marketing%20staff%20and%20other%20positions%2C%20said%20Shull.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShifting%20demographics%20within%20the%20US%20workforce%20and%20continued%20low%20unemployment%20mean%20Boeing%20will%20face%20more%20competition%20when%20it%20needs%20to%20resume%20hiring%20to%20support%20its%20growth%2C%20said%20Richard%20Aboulafia%2C%20a%20managing%20director%20with%20AeroDynamic%20Advisory.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20works%20fine%20as%20long%20as%20labor%20markets%20aren't%20tight%2C%26quot%3B%20Aboulafia%20said%20in%20an%20interview.%20%26quot%3BBut%20aerospace%20and%20defense%20labor%20markets%20are%20really%20tight.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBesides%2C%20rolling%20out%20blanket%20workforce%20cuts%20are%20%26quot%3Bthe%20surest%20formula%20for%20losing%2010%25%20of%20your%20best%20people%26quot%3B%20who%20will%20gravitate%20to%20potentially%20more%20stable%20employers%2C%20Aboulafia%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20lost%20institutional%20knowledge%20was%20apparent%20as%20the%20company%20made%20only%20halting%20progress%20ramping%20up%20manufacturing%20of%20its%20737%20Max%20jetliner%20this%20decade.%20Executives%20later%20acknowledged%20they'd%20underestimated%20the%20training%20required%20to%20bring%20the%20large%20influx%20of%20new%20hires%20up%20to%20speed%20in%20their%20factories.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Reset%20Priorities'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20so%2C%20the%20company%20is%20staffed%20for%20peak%20production%20levels%20it%20likely%20won't%20see%20for%20years%2C%20especially%20after%20a%2053-day%20strike%20largely%20halted%20work%20in%20its%20plants%20across%20the%20west%20coast.%20Boeing%20had%20171%2C000%20employees%20at%20the%20start%20of%20this%20year%2C%2012%25%20more%20than%20the%20153%2C000%20it%20employed%20five%20years%20earlier%2C%20when%20its%20factories%20were%20at%20their%20pre-crisis%20peak.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERelations%20between%20workers%20and%20Boeing%20hit%20a%20low%20during%20the%20strike%20that%20just%20ended.%20Boeing%20was%20finally%20able%20to%20settle%20the%20dispute%20with%20concessions%20including%20a%2038%25%20wage%20improvement%2C%20but%20many%20employees%20remain%20antagonized%20by%20a%20company%20they%20say%20has%20not%20paid%20them%20fairly%20for%20years.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKelly%20Ortberg%2C%20who%20was%20hired%20in%20August%20as%20chief%20executive%20officer%20to%20turn%20around%20Boeing%2C%20has%20said%20the%2010%25%20workforce%20reduction%20is%20part%20of%20a%20broader%20campaign%20to%20cut%20out%20bloat%20and%20inefficiency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20need%20to%20reset%20priorities%20and%20create%20a%20leaner%2C%20more%20focused%20organization%2C%26quot%3B%20Ortberg%20said%20during%20an%20Oct.%2023%20earnings%20call.%20The%20cuts%20are%20intended%20to%2