nema%20debuts.%20Prime%20Video%20acquired%20the%20OTT%20rights%20for%20a%20record-breaking%20Rs%20100%20crore%2C%20with%20a%20planned%20release%20during%20Pongal%2C%20eight%20weeks%20after%20its%20theatrical%20run.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20Entertainment%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Ftamil%2Fmovies%2Fnews%2Fkanguva-ott-release-date-when-and-where-can-we-expect-suriyas-periodic-action-drama%2Farticleshow%2F115288225.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20Much%20Money%20Do%20You%20Need%20To%20Afford%20A%20House%20In%20US%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EWant%20to%20buy%20a%20home%20in%20the%20United%20States%3F%20Well%2C%20think%20about%20it%20only%20if%20you%20earn%20at%20least%20%241%2C08%2C000%20(around%20Rs%2091.15%20lakh)%20or%20more%2C%20a%20report%20said.%20This%20change%2C%20highlighted%20in%20a%20recent%20report%20from%20Oxford%20Economics%2C%20underscores%20the%20rapid%20shift%20in%20the%20housing%20market.%20In%20the%20third%20quarter%20of%202024%2C%20only%2036%25%20of%20US%20households%20had%20enough%20income%20to%20afford%20a%20new%20home%2C%20compared%20to%2059%25%20in%20the%20same%20period%20five%20years%20ago.%20This%20sharp%20decline%20reflects%20the%20challenges%20many%20Americans%20now%20face%20buying%20a%20property.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20numbers%20are%20in%20stark%20contrast%20to%20just%20a%20few%20years%20ago.%20In%202019%2C%20a%20household%20needed%20only%20%2456%2C800%20(around%20Rs%2048%20lakh)%20to%20comfortably%20cover%20the%20cost%20of%20a%20new%20single-family%20home%2C%20including%20property%20taxes%20and%20insurance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20massive%20surge%20in%20housing%20prices%20over%20the%20last%20five%20years%20is%20largely%20due%20to%20the%20disruption%20caused%20by%20the%20pandemic.%20During%20COVID-19%2C%20many%20Americans%20sought%20larger%20homes%2C%20leading%20to%20a%20surge%20in%20demand.%20Simultaneously%2C%20the%20country%20experienced%20a%20shortage%20of%20available%20homes%2C%20which%2C%20combined%20with%20rising%20demand%2C%20pushed%20home%20prices%20to%20new%20heights.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20affordability%20crisis%20is%20most%20apparent%20in%20certain%20cities.%20San%20Jose%2C%20California%2C%20for%20example%2C%20has%20become%20the%20least%20affordable%20metro%20area%20in%20the%20US%2C%20with%20a%20median%20house%20price%20of%20%241.89%20million%20(around%20Rs%2016%20crore).%20To%20afford%20a%20home%20there%2C%20a%20household%20would%20need%20to%20earn%20%244%2C61%2C000%20(Rs%203.89%20crore)%20annually.%20Other%20major%20California%20cities%20such%20as%20San%20Francisco%2C%20Los%20Angeles%20and%20San%20Diego%20also%20rank%20among%20the%20least%20affordable%20regions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECleveland%2C%20Louisville%2C%20Detroit%20and%20St.%20Louis%20were%20among%20the%20more%20affordable%20cities%2C%20where%20households%20needed%20an%20income%20ranging%20from%20%2464%2C600%20to%20%2475%2C300%20(Rs%2054%20lakh%20to%20Rs%2064%20lakh)%20to%20manage%20housing%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOxford%20Economics%20defines%20a%20home%20as%20affordable%20if%20the%20monthly%20payment%20does%20not%20exceed%2028%25%20of%20a%20person's%20income.%20%E2%80%9CWhile%20house%20prices%20increased%20in%20every%20metro%2C%20the%20rise%20in%20mortgage%20rates%20eroded%20affordability%20more%20significantly%20as%20rates%20nearly%20doubled%20from%203.7%25%20in%20Q3%202019%20to%20a%20high%20of%207.3%25%20in%20Q4%202023%2C%E2%80%9D%20Barbara%20Denham%2C%20a%20senior%20economist%20at%20Oxford%20Economics%2C%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fedition.cnn.com%2F2024%2F11%2F13%2Feconomy%2Fhome-buyer-salary-household-income%2Findex.html%5C%22%3ECNN%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1731570000000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2020-08%2Fc4qfcckk_new-york-generic_625x300_13_August_20.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.n