as%20long%20dominated%20the%20rare%20earths%20market%20due%20to%20supply%2C%20low%20labor%20costs%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fmarkets%2Fcommodities%2Fchinas-rare-earths-dominance-focus-after-mineral-export-curbs-2023-07-05%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elax%20environmental%20standards.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20country%20produces%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iea.org%2Freports%2Fenergy-technology-perspectives-2023%2Fclean-energy-supply-chains-vulnerabilities%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%2060%25%20of%20the%20world's%20rare%20earth%20mineral%20supply%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20accounts%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iea.org%2Freports%2Fthe-role-of-critical-minerals-in-clean-energy-transitions%2Fexecutive-summary%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E90%25%20of%20global%20refined%20output.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20late%20Deng%20Xiaoping%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Chinese%20leader%20who%20spearheaded%20the%20country's%20economic%20reforms%20in%201978%20%E2%80%94%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnm.cnr.cn%2Fnmzt%2F60dq%2Ftjnmg%2F200704%2Ft20070412_504442760.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20recognized%20their%20strategic%20importance%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%201992%2C%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20Middle%20East%20has%20oil%2C%20China%20has%20rare%20earths.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20new%20regulations%20introduced%20last%20month%2C%20China's%20rare%20earth%20resources%20now%20belong%20to%20the%20state.%20Two%20Canadian-owned%20rare%20earth%20refineries%20in%20China%20are%20also%20being%20acquired%20by%20state-owned%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20not%20the%20first%20time%20Beijing%20has%20placed%20restrictions%20on%20rare%20earths.%20In%202010%2C%20China%20imposed%20strict%20rare%20earth%20quotas%2C%20citing%20environmental%20concerns%20and%20resource%20preservation.%20The%20move%20sent%20prices%20up%20sharply%20and%20prompted%20the%20US%2C%20the%20European%20Union%2C%20and%20Japan%20to%20file%20a%20complaint%20against%20China%20for%20unfair%20trade%20practices%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wto.org%2Fenglish%2Ftratop_e%2Fdispu_e%2Fcases_e%2Fds431_e.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWorld%20Trade%20Organization%3C%2Fa%3E.%20China%20lost%20the%20case%20and%20lifted%20exported%20quotas%20in%202015.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVarious%20countries%20tried%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.circularise.com%2Fblogs%2Fthe-rare-earth-problem-sustainable-sourcing-and-supply-chain-challenges%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ediversify%3C%2Fa%3E%20their%20rare%20earth%20supply%20chains%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20China's%20quotas%20in%20the%202010s%2C%20but%20success%20has%20been%20limited%20due%20to%20the%20high%20cost%20of%20investment%20and%20environmental%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20renewed%20efforts%20to%20boost%20global%20production%20in%20the%20face%20of%20rising%20tensions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20the%20US%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whitehouse.gov%2Fbriefing-room%2Fstatements-releases%2F2024%2F09%2F20%2Ffact-sheet-biden-harris-administration-takes-further-action-to-strengthen-and-secure-critical-mineral-supply-chains%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDepartment%20of%20Defense%3C%2Fa%3E%20awarded%20%2445%20million%20to%20MP%20Materials%20for%20rare%20earth%20oxide%20processing%2C%20and%20in%202023%2C%20it%20awarded%20over%20%24288%20million%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessdefense.gov%2Fnews%2F2023%2FDoD-Awards-Key-Contract-for-Domestic-Heavy-Rare-Earth-Separation-Capability.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELynas%20USA%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20set%20up%20commercial-scale%20rare%20earth%20oxide%20production%20facilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c8073b51-666c-4b37-8da2-99bb4249c25d%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20is%20China%20leveraging%20rare%20earths%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBeijing's%20moves%20to%20control%20critical%20minerals%20and%20rare%20earths%20are%20part%20of%20a%20toolbox%20Beijing%20has%20developed%20over%20the%20last%20four%20years%2C%20Rick%20Waters%2C%20the%20managing%20director%20of%20Eurasia%20Group's%20China%20practice%2C%20said%20at%20a%20press%20briefing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20President%20Donald%20Trump's%20first%20term%2C%20the%20US%20and%20China%20slapped%20retaliatory%20tariffs%20on%20each%20other.%20However%2C%20China%20has%20less%20leverage%20in%20a%20tariff%20fight%20because%20it%20exports%20more%20to%20the%20US%20than%20it%20imports%2C%20so%20it%20came%20up%20with%20another%20regulatory%20framework%20%E2%80%94%20this%20one%20involving%20rare%20earths%20%E2%80%94%20that%20it%20can%20use%20in%20a%20trade%20dispute.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20experimenting%20with%20its%20use%2C%20and%20I%20think%2C%20in%20a%20way%2C%20they%20could%20go%20further%20%E2%80%94%20if%20they%20perceive%20they%20need%20to%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Waters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAny%20further%20tightening%20of%20rare%20earth%20supplies%20%E2%80%94%20which%20are%20a%20subset%20under%20critical%20minerals%20%E2%80%94%20could%20leave%20the%20US%20vulnerable%20to%20supply%20shocks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BChina%20has%20cornered%20the%20market%20for%20processing%20and%20refining%20of%20key%20critical%20minerals%2C%20leaving%20the%20US%20and%20our%20allies%20and%20partners%20vulnerable%20to%20supply%20chain%20shocks%20and%20undermining%20economic%20and%20national%20security%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20White%20House%20said%20in%20a%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whitehouse.gov%2Fbriefing-room%2Fstatements-releases%2F2024%2F09%2F20%2Ffact-sheet-biden-harris-administration-takes-further-action-to-strengthen-and-secure-critical-mineral-supply-chains%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20statement%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20September.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a846860e-2bcb-4815-adc9-5f8fef9eaa09%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20do%20the%20restrictions%20on%20rare%20earths%20mean%20for%20TSMC%20and%20Nvidia%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EChina's%20control%20over%20rare%20earths%20could%20weigh%20heavily%20in%20the%20trade%20war%20between%20Washington%20and%20Beijing%2C%20with%20chips%20in%20the%20center%20of%20the%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChips%20are%20found%20in%20everything%20from%20computers%20to%20cell%20phones%2C%20cars%2C%20and%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-rare-earth-minerals-stockpile-mystery-opacity-worries-experts-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20defense%20equipment%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Taiwan%20dominates%20the%20market%2C%20producing%20over%2060%25%20of%20the%20world's%20chips%20and%20over%2090%25%20of%20the%20most%20advanced%20ones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20company%20%E2%80%94%20Taiwan%20Semiconductor%20Manufacturing%20Company%20%E2%80%94%20is%20responsible%20for%20most%20of%20the%20output%20and%20is%20the%20key%20supplier%20to%20AI%20chip%20giant%20Nvidia%2C%20which%20is%20in%20the%20thick%20of%20the%20tech%20rivalry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20has%20already%20moved%20to%20block%20the%20export%20of%20advanced%20chips%20and%20chipmaking%20equipment%20to%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20trade%20tiff%20escalates%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20in%20the%20form%20of%20higher%20tariffs%20%E2%80%94%20China%20could%20pull%20its%20rare%20earth%20card%2C%20Oxford%20Economics%20wrote%20in%20a%20report%20published%20in%20July.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BChina's%20dominance%20in%20the%20battery%20supply%20chain%20accords%20policymakers%20with%20leverage%20to%20withhold%20industry-specific%20inputs%20from%20Western%20manufacturers%2C%20which%20could%20prove%20inflationary%20and%20economically%20disruptive%2C%26quot%3B%20wrote%20Louise%20Loo%2C%20the%20lead%20economist%20for%20Greater%20China%20at%20Oxford%20Economics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20could%20involve%20further%20controls%20on%20critical%20commodity%20exports%2C%20particularly%20in%20rare%20earth%20minerals%2C%20Loo%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20happened%20with%20China's%20rare%20earth%20export%20curbs%20in%202010%2C%20prices%20are%20likely%20to%20spike%20if%20supply%20is%20tightened%2C%20so%20any%20prolonged%20supply%20crunch%20could%20drive%20up%20inflation%20for%20end%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2241f10c92-fd52-4452-af13-c2607b378399%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20tech%20Cold%20War%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20and%20China's%20moves%20to%20outmaneuver%20each%20other%20in%20the%20tech%20race%20have%20some%20analysts%20drawing%20parallels%20to%20the%20Cold%20War.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZongyuan%20Zoe%20Liu%2C%20a%20senior%20fellow%20for%20China%20studies%20at%20the%20Council%20on%20Foreign%20Relations%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20the%20idea%20that%20the%20US%20ought%20to%20out-compete%20China%20and%20prevent%20the%20nation%20from%20developing%20advanced%20chips%20plays%20into%20a%20%26quot%3Bbigger%20power%20competition%20narrative.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20the%20tensions%20are%20similar%2C%20though%20not%20identical%2C%20to%20the%20tensions%20between%20the%20US%20and%20Soviet%20Union%20that%20began%20after%20the%20end%20of%20World%20War%20II.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2024-10-15%2Fus-weighs-capping-exports-of-ai-chips-from-nvidia-and-amd-to-some-countries%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Bloomberg%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%20last%20month%2C%20the%20US%20is%20considering%20limiting%20export%20licenses%20for%20both%20Nvidia%20and%20AMD%20chips%20in%20an%20unfolding%20trade%20war%20that%20has%20also%20hit%20several%20sensitive%20industries%2C%20including%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhite-house-joe-biden-hikes-tariffs-on-chinese-made-evs-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20electric%20vehicles%2C%20batteries%2C%20and%20some%20solar%20panels.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20imposed%20similar%20trade%20limits%2C%20embargoes%2C%20and%20economic%20sanctions%20on%20the%20Soviet%20Union%2C%20North%20Korea%2C%20China%2C%20and%20North%20Vietnam%20during%20the%20Cold%20War.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20the%20heart%20of%20the%20issue%20is%20concern%20about%20how%20China%20will%20use%20AI%20chips%20for%20military%20applications%20and%20surveillance%2C%26quot%3B%20Chris%20Tang%2C%20a%20UCLA%20professor%20and%20expert%20in%20global%20supply%20chain%20management%20and%20the%20impact%20of%20regulatory%20policies%2C%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20different%20type%20of%20Cold%20War.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20a%20tense%20relationship%2C%20the%20dynamics%20between%20the%20US%20and%20China%20are%20also%20creating%20parallel%20systems%2C%20with%20the%20US%20and%20its%20allies%20on%20one%20side%2C%20and%20China%20and%20its%20allies%20on%20the%20other%2C%20Nick%20Vyas%2C%20the%20founding%20director%20of%20USC%20Marshall's%20Randall%20R.%20Kendrick%20Global%20Supply%20Chain%20Institute%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVyas%20said%20he's%20concerned%20the%20tension%20could%20escalate%20from%20this%20new%20Cold%20War%20to%20a%20hot%20one%20between%20global%20powers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20we%20stop%20transacting%20horizontally%20with%20each%20other%2C%20that's%20only%20creating%20a%20larger%20conflict%2C%26quot%3B%20Vyas%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20then%20with%20a%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fseal-team-6-fight-with-china-over-taiwan-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20South%20China%20Sea%20conflict%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20geopolitical%20conflict%20could%20turn%20into%20a%20larger%20conflict%2C%20which%20can%20lead%20to%20a%20major%20situation%20that%20leads%20up%20to%20a%20war.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepresentatives%20for%20Nvidia%20declined%20to%20comment%20for%20this%20story.%20Representatives%20for%20AMD%20and%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Industry%20and%20Security%20didn't%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment%20from%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http